76561198043450023,Recommended,503340,24962560,"Posted: 16 August, 2016",all,ownedbytamater,"Dig for Destruction is going to be HUGE!I think this is the only game that had me laughing and giggling while still playing the tutorial!I can't wait for more people to be online so that I can get into some good multiplayer matches!This game is great, the fast paced quirky style that it brings to the table keeps things feeling light and fun (even if you're getting destroyed) but and the same time giving you a reason to try.Essentially you dig through the ground with your hands while you move forward. You use your sonar to scan for weapons and enemies. It's very straightforward and easy to pickup for anyone.  Even if you are the best player ever you will die plenty and even if you are the worst...well you will probably get kills because that damn rocket launcher is so op if you get to it's spawn.In all seriousness this game will be a very fun game to pick up and play a few games at a time and then put down and come back later. There is loads of replayability in this game.The game feels like it could be a lot like rec room in regards to the social environment. The waiting area puts all the players qued up for the match in the same room where you can play chess, light fireworks, break ceiling fans (oops I mean shoot basketball), look in the mirror at yourself, and loads more.There is in game voice chat so that you don't have to rely on gestures. I feel that in a game like this both social and competitive voice chat is something that is greatly needed. Without it you can't hear the person laughing on the other end which in turn makes you laugh and then everyones laughing at something that had there been no voice chat wouldn't have even been that great.As you complete achievements you unlock new masks to put on your head, esentially it's your in game avatar.When you jump into a game you spawn in seperate corners and you start digging towards weapons. You can take your opponnents weapons from them if you're close enough as well! The whole game is so energetic and funny that it just works! There are several different weapons to use and try out, my personal favorite being the frying pan!I can't wait for more updates and players online!In case you want to see the game in action linked below is my gameplay commentary of Dig 4 Destruction. Enjoy!http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=745797705"
